		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Mortgage</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about the legal mechanisms used to secure the performance of obligations, including the payment of debts, with property.  For loans secured by mortgages, such as residential housing loans, and lending practices or requirements, see <a href="/wiki/Mortgage_loan" title="Mortgage loan">Mortgage loan</a>.</div>
