<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> The failure to record a previously made mortgage may, under some circumstances, allow a subsequent mortgagee's mortgage to be recognized as prior in right to the otherwise prior mortgage.</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Of course, the lienholders can agree among themselves to a different priority arrangement through <a href="/wiki/Subordination_(finance)" title="Subordination (finance)">subordination arrangements</a>. See, R. Kratovil and R. Werner <i>Modern Mortgage Law and Practice</i> Chs. 30 &amp; 38 (2nd Ed. Prentice-Hall, Inc.)</li>
